article.headline: Xavier 82, Eastern Kentucky 63
article.story: CINCINNATI (AP) -- Brian Thornton's 25 points and nine rebounds led Xavier to a 82-63 win Monday night over Eastern Kentucky. The Musketeers (10-2) dominated the Colonels (6-8) down low, outscoring them 38-18 in the paint. Xavier also scored 21 points off 19 Colonels turnovers and got 25 points from the bench to Eastern Kentucky's 14. Justin Doellman had 15 points and five assists while Stanley Burrell added 11 points and six rebounds for Xavier. Eastern Kentucky's Matt Witt went 7-for-10 from the 3-point line on the way to a game-high 27 points. He also had seven assists and five rebounds. The Colonels also got 11 points from Jason McLeish. Xavier led 32-28 at halftime but outscored Eastern Kentucky by 15 points in the second half.
